data.title: Private Mumbai Sightseeing Tour (Traveller's Choice Award Winner)
data.description: Booking our city sightseeing tour is a great way to explore and experience the vibrant city of Mumbai. Our knowledgeable and friendly tour guides, who are Mumbai University students, will take you to the top attractions of the city such as the Gateway of India, Marine Drive, Crawford Market, and many more. data.title: (Mysuru) Mysore Day Out - A Royal Experience Private Tour from Bangalore
data.description:
Perfect day tour for visiting Mysore. Private day tour starts from 7:30 in the morning and continues till evening. Tourists visit the Magnificent Mysore Palace, the legendary Chamundi Hills, Somnathpur Temple & Daria Daulat. 
Mysore beautifully showcases Indian history, how the Wadiyar dynasty ruled Mysore, How it was invaded and what happened to this city after the tragedy.

An epic story filled with Indian culture and history. During the tour, we will make you try Indian cuisine and explore the food joints which have the mesmerizing Indian aroma and make you experience the Indian culture that you would have never seen before!

So are you ready for an Indian history bomb been thrown at you?!

Note:- For this Royal Mysore trip you can choose any one of the options mentioned below:
*Mysore Palace, Dariya Daula, Devaraj Market, Colonel Belly Dungeon.
*Mysore Palace, Sand Museum, Devaraj Market and Chamundi hills.
*Mysore Palace, Sand Museum, Devaraj Market and Somnathpur Temple.

data.title: Elephanta Caves & Island Guided Private Tour
data.description: The Elephanta Caves are situated in Western India on Elephanta Island (also called the Island of Gharapuri), which highlights two hillocks isolated by a tight valley. The little island is dabbed with various old archeological remaining parts that are the sole declarations to its rich social past. These archeological remaining parts uncover proof of occupation from as soon as the second century BC. The stone cut Elephanta Caves were built about the mid-fifth to sixth hundreds of years AD. The most significant among the caverns is the incomparable Cave 1, which estimates 39 meters from the front access to the back. In plan, this cavern in the western slope intently looks like Dumar Lena cave at Ellora, in India. The principal body of the cavern, barring the porches on the three open sides and the back passageway, is 27 meters square and is upheld by lines of six sections each. Elephanta Caves are an UNESCO World Heritage Site.

data.title: Dharavi slum tour by the 1st female tour guide of Mumbai's slum
data.description: Booking a Dharavi slum tour offers a unique and eye-opening experience for visitors to Mumbai. It provides an opportunity to learn about the culture, lifestyle, and resilience of the people living in one of Asia's largest slums. The tour is guided by local residents who can provide an authentic perspective on life in the slum. Additionally, a portion of the proceeds from the tour goes towards supporting community development projects in the area. By booking a Dharavi slum tour, visitors can gain a deeper understanding and appreciation of the city of Mumbai and it's diverse communities.

data.title: 3-Day Private Taj Mahal, Agra and Delhi Tour from Goa or Mumbai
data.description: A trip to India is considered incomplete without visiting the spectacular monument that lies in Agra, the Taj Mahal, one of the Seven Wonders of the World. This 3-day tour is specially designed for tourists who arrive to enjoy the fascinating beaches of Goa for several weeks, so that they may also have the opportunity to make a pilgrimage to the Taj Mahal and visit other attractions in Delhi and Agra, such as the Agra Fort and Mehtab Bagh. In Delhi, you will have the chance to visit the 11th Century Qutub Minar, built by Qutub-ud-din Aibek of the Slave Dynasty, Humayun's Tomb, the Bahai Temple, also known as the Lotus Temple and the war memorial, India Gate. You will also drive by the Parliament House, the President's Palace and the Secretariat buildings.

data.title: Tour Guatapé
data.description:
Only an hour and a half from the city of Medellin, is the place most visited by our travelers, La Piedra del Peñol, one of the most beautiful monoliths of the world with 220 meters of height and an unparalleled view of the Peñol-Guatape reservoir. 

In this experience you will enjoy an unforgettable landscape while traveling by boat one of the most important dams that contribute to the energetic supply of Colombia. You will also have the possibility to climb the 740 steps that take you to one of the most impressive views of the reservoir. To culminate the day perfectly, you will explore one of the most colorful and beautiful villages of our country where you will cross the street of memories, the plaza of the zócalos, the boardwalk and its main park.

data.title: Four-Day Private Luxury Golden Triangle Tour to Agra and Jaipur From New Delhi
data.description: Explore India's Golden Triangle on this four-day private tour traveling by air-conditioned vehicle with a local guide. In Delhi, visit Qutb Minar, Lotus Temple, India Gate, and Parliament House. Watch the sun rise over the Taj Mahal, visit Agra’s Red Fort and Baby Taj. In Jaipur, visit Panna Meena Ka Kund (Step well), Amber Fort, Jal Mahal, Palace of Winds, Maharaja's City Palace, and Jantar Mantar Observatory. Three nights of five-star accommodations, breakfasts, transportation, and guided tours are included. You’ll sample local dishes for lunch and dinner on your own, and cover your own monument entrance fees.

data.title: 3-Day Private Luxury Golden Triangle Tour to Agra and Jaipur From New Delhi
data.description: Explore India’s Golden Triangle, including Delhi, Agra and Jaipur, on this private 3-day tour from New Delhi. Visit the 11th-century UNESCO World Heritage Site Qutub Minar, The Bahai Temple that is also known as the Lotus Temple, and the India Gate. Drive by the Parliament House, the President's Palace, and the Secretariat buildings. Experience the Taj Mahal and Red Fort in Agra. In Jaipur, discover the Amber Fort, Water Palace, City Palace, Jantar Mantar and Hawa Mahal. Travel comfortably in a private climate-controlled vehicle with a guide.

data.title: Private tour: GIza Pyramids, Memphis City & Sakkara Pyramid
data.description: Embark on a captivating private tour tailored to inspire and enrich. Our expert guides will take you on an exciting exploration of the iconic GIZA PYRAMIDS, where you can admire the grandeur of these ancient marvellous structures. The tour then unfolds the vibrant history of MEMPHIS CITY, the ancient capital of Egypt, revealing its precious archaeological gems. Finally, stand before the timeless majesty of the SAKKARA PYRAMID, a crucial testament to the evolution of pyramid construction. This private tour encapsulates Egypt's golden age while offering you the freedom and personalized attention only a private tour can provide.

data.title: 5 Days Private Heritage Triangle Tour Jaipur, Jodhpur, Udaipur.
data.description:
Rajasthan golden triangle is a tourist circuit which connects the Jaipur, Jodhpur and Udaipur. The Rajasthan Triangle is so called because of the triangular shape formed by the locations of Jaipur, Jodhpur and Udaipur in Rajasthan map. The trips usually start in Jaipur moving west to the site of Jodhpur, then South East, to the Lake City of Rajasthan i.e. Udaipur.

Tour Highlights 
Visit & Enjoy best Heritage Cities of Rajasthan
Tour by Private transportation 
Visit Jaipur, a heritage pink city of india
Visit historical & heritage forts in all three cities
Enjoy Rickshaw ride in Pinkcity jaipur 
Enjoy Street Food in Jaipur 
Visit Pushkar, on the way to Jodhpur 
Visit Jodhpur, an blue city
Visit & Enjoy Udaipur, Known as City of lakes
